reviews.text:
The Epitome of a Summer Moment.

Ah yes, Good Eats and Sips, from bagels and bowls to coffees and this wonderful drink ( Under the Sea Lemonade ) , this is an absolute stand out restaurant. My advice, order on the Local app and walk across the street to Clift Park....and just savior not Just your treat but the "Moment"
My family members have been eating here and taking meals to go for four years, and we love  it!  There‚Äôs always something delicious for everyone. The food and staff are wonderful!

I got the Baang Salad and my dad got noodles. My salad was very nicely seasoned and my dad seemed to enjoy his noodles. Maybe a bit expensive, but around normal price for that kind of salad and I don‚Äôt mind as long as it has good ingredients and production.

Nice staff, pretty good atmosphere. Lovely place. We went around 2 though, so it might be better to skip this place if it gets too busy, it seems like pretty minimal staffing, but there seems to be an online order system which seems nice to use.

Also, there isn‚Äôt a tray return, apparently they‚Äôre just supposed to be left at the table.

Wish this place was open later in the summer‚Äî such a perfect spot to grab food. I only wish the place was bigger. Skaneateles lake is 20 steps away so we get food for takeout a lot of the time and sit by the water. Delicious, healthy, and dietary restriction friendly. Only complaint is that it‚Äôs a little pricey but expected for the touristy area.
